{"id": 685, "date": "1987-03-14T11:00:31", "date_gmt": "1987-03-14T19:00:31", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=685"}, "modified": "2026-06-09T17:07:07", "modified_gmt": "2026-06-10T00:07:07", "slug": "matr-bruce-springsteen-and-nicky-addeo-the-night-owls-whats-your-name", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1987/03/14/matr-bruce-springsteen-and-nicky-addeo-the-night-owls-whats-your-name/", "title": {"rendered": "What&#8217;s Your Name"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>On April 2, 2011, Nicky Addeo and the Night Owls played the Wonder Bar in Asbury Park.</p>\n<p>Nicky Addeo isn&#8217;t a household name, but in 1963 he released a song called &#8220;Gloria&#8221; with The Darchaes, and Bruce was a big fan of it.</p>\n<p>&#8220;When you wanted to make your move, you waited for Nicky Addeo to sing <a href=\"https://youtu.be/7TSwtof6LTQ\">Gloria</a>,&#8221; Bruce explained that evening in Asbury Park. Bruce got a chance to play the song with Nicky that night, and he stayed on stage for several songs, including &#8220;What&#8217;s Your Name?&#8221;</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/GbhmYTRWtCo?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>&#8220;What&#8217;s Your Name&#8221; was released in 1962 by Don and Juan. It was their only hit, reaching #7 on the Billboard pop chart. The boys&#8217; cover is pretty true to the original.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/vrZf3vRHmkw?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p><strong>What&#8217;s Your Name<br />\nFirst performed:\u00a0</strong>October 1965 (Monmouth County, NJ)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> April 2, 2011 (Asbury Park, NJ)</p>\n<p>\u00a9 February 18, 2018</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>Bruce and Nicky Addeo and the Night Owls croon a soulful cover of &#8220;What&#8217;s Your Name?&#8221; at the Stone Pony.</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 69814, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "_jetpack_newsletter_access": "", "_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content": false, "_jetpack_feature_clip_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content": false, "footnotes": "", "jetpack_publicize_message": "", "jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled": true, "jetpack_social_post_already_shared": true, "jetpack_social_options": {"image_generator_settings": {"template": "highway", "default_image_id": 0, "font": "", "enabled": false}, "version": 2}, "jetpack_post_was_ever_published": false}, "categories": [3617, 5], "tags": [324, 323], "class_list": ["post-685", "post", "type-post", "status-publish", "format-standard", "has-post-thumbnail", "hentry", "category-it-takes-two", "category-meeting-across-the-river", "tag-nicky-addeo", "t